1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 Bf5 5. Nc3 e6 6. Nh4 Be4 7. f3 Bg6 8. Bd2 Be7 9. Nxg6 hxg6 10. Qc2 a5 $5 { the starting point of this chapter. Black wants to meet 0-0-0 with dxc4 followed by b5-a4. This is not very popular, but I find this to be a very challenging idea. } 11. h4 $5 { gaining space on the other flank of the board } 11... Nbd7 { the most principled response. Black develops the last minor piece. } ( { trying to exploit the weaknesses with } 11... Nh5 { looks very strong, but in fact is a slight inaccuracy. Bxh4 opens up the h-file for the rook thus giving us options like g4, while we deal with the threat of Ng3 with } 12. Ne2 { [%cal Ge2g3] } 12... Bxh4+ { the critical response. } ( 12... dxc4 13. Qxc4 Nf6 14. e4 { [%cal Ge1c1,Ya2a3] followed by 0-0-0. Keep in mind that we might play a3 to stop b5-b4.Black has to be very accurate here. } ) 13. Kd1 { [%csl Re8] And the threat of g4 is awkward to face. } 13... Rh7 { what else? } ( 13... O-O $4 14. g4 Ng3 15. Nxg3 Bxg3 16. f4 $18 { [%csl Rg3][%cal Gg4g5,Gh1h3] } ) 14. Qb3 $16 { [%csl Re8][%cal Ge3e4,Yc4d5] } ) ( 11... Na6 { is comfortably met with } 12. a3 $14 ) ( 11... dxc4 { was tried by Alireza in the only OTB game in this line. } 12. Bxc4 Nd5 ( 12... Nbd7 13. Ne2 { [%cal Ye1c1,Gc4e6] Sneakily preparing Be6. Even if don't get that, we keep the option of 0-0-0. White has an easier game due to pair of bishops and space. } ) 13. g3 $14 { [%cal Ge1f2,Ye3e4,Yh4h5] this novelty give white a very decent position. We want to play Kf2 next, and then open up the kingside or expand the centre. } ) 12. O-O-O { [%cal Yg2g4] We finish developing and are all set to play g4 next. Therefore, black needs to start their own play with } 12... dxc4 13. Bxc4 a4 { however, after } 14. Kb1 { we have significantly easier play. Some sample lines- } 14... a3 ( 14... Nb6 15. Bf1 $14 ) 15. b3 Bb4 $1 ( 15... Nb6 16. Bf1 $1 { [%cal Ye7b4,Gc3e2] Keeping the e2 square for knight after Bb4 } ) 16. e4 Nb6 17. g3 $14 { Concrete mode again. White is better strategically so black needs to be very precise } *
