1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 Nbd7 { the best sideline from's point of view in this chapter. } ( 4... dxc4 $6 5. Bxc4 e6 6. O-O c5 7. Nc3 $16 { [%cal Yd1e2,Yf1d1] gives us a version of the QGA with an extra tempo. } ) ( 4... Qb6 { has been tried by Hikaru and Kamsky, but looks unimpressive. We can continue normally with } 5. Nc3 Bg4 ( 5... Bf5 6. Ne5 $16 ) 6. h3 Bxf3 7. Qxf3 $14 { [%cal Gf1d3,Ge1g1] } ) 5. Bd3 $5 { a clever move. We are waiting for black to commit to either e6, or g6. } ( 5. Nc3 e6 { transposes to the Meran system. } ) ( 5. b3 g6 $1 ) 5... e6 ( 5... g6 { is now met with } 6. Nc3 $14 { with the point that after } 6... Bg7 { we have } 7. cxd5 cxd5 8. Qb3 { [%csl Rd7] exploiting the poor positioning of the d7-knight. } 8... Nb8 9. Bd2 Nc6 10. O-O O-O 11. Rfc1 $14 { [%cal Ga2a4,Gb3a3,Ga4a5,Yd3b5] } ) ( 5... dxc4 6. Bxc4 $14 ) 6. b3 $1 { the right time. } 6... Bb4+ { the critical independent try. Black tries to exploit our move order. } ( 6... Bd6 7. Bb2 O-O 8. Nbd2 { transposes to variations covered via the 4...e6 move order. } ) 7. Nbd2 Ne4 { [%csl Rd2] the most ambitious attempt. Black puts pressure on our d2-knight. } ( 7... Bc3 { intending to meet } 8. Rb1 { with } 8... e5 $5 { striking the centre. This is possible, but not something we should be afraid about. } 9. dxe5 Nxe5 10. Nxe5 Bxe5 11. Qc2 O-O 12. O-O { [%cal Yd2f3,Yc1b2] we are now looking to develop normally with Nf3-Bb2. } 12... Re8 ( 12... Qe7 { takes the eye away from the d5-pawn, allowing us to play } 13. cxd5 cxd5 14. Bb2 $14 ) 13. Nf3 Bd6 14. Bb2 $1 { we tempt black to play } 14... Ne4 { which we meet with } ( 14... dxc4 15. bxc4 $16 { [%csl Rb7][%cal Gc4c5, Yb2d4] } ) ( 14... h6 15. cxd5 Nxd5 16. h3 $14 { [%cal Yb1d1,Yf3d4,Yh3g4,Rc8g4] } ) 15. Rfd1 Qe7 16. cxd5 cxd5 17. Bb5 $14 { [%csl Rd5] with a small advantage. } ) 8. a3 $1 Bc3 ( 8... Nxd2 $6 9. axb4 Nxf3+ 10. Qxf3 $16 { [%csl Gb4,Gc1,Gc4,Gd3,Gd4] } ) ( 8... Bxd2+ 9. Nxd2 $16 { [%csl Gc1,Gd3] } ) 9. Ra2 $1 { [%cal Ya2d2] } 9... Ba5 $5 { [%cal Ye4c3] } ( { the thematic } 9... e5 { runs into } 10. cxd5 cxd5 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Nxe5 Bxe5 13. Nxe4 dxe4 14. Bxe4 Qxd1+ 15. Kxd1 $14 { with good practical chances for white thanks to the extra pawn } ) 10. Bb2 f5 11. b4 Bc7 12. a4 $14 { [%cal Ya4a5,Yb4b5] } *
